## Testing Expectations by Area

- **`cli.py`**: Parser contracts, required args, flag defaults, command dispatch.
- **`config.py`** and **`domain/models.py`**: Dataclass defaults, type/shape invariants, validation (e.g. `ReviewAction.validate`).
- **`gnucash/loader.py`**: Fixture-driven XML parse/write using `sample_gnucash_path`; no-book and write-changes error paths; `get_tree()` / `get_account_path` defaults.
- **`email/*`**: Parse and body-filtering tests using `tests/fixtures/emails/`; missing file raises; index build skips corrupt lines and unparseable .eml.
- **`receipt/*`**: Programmatically generated images (Pillow); `FileNotFoundError` and unsupported format; repository `list_unprocessed` when dir missing.
- **`matching/*`**: Deterministic scoring with constructed evidence; tolerance-zero; no-amount exclusion.
- **`ml/predictor.py`**: Training edge cases; LLM path mocked; `get_emails_for_display` (including empty list); run_llm_check/flow None and fallbacks.
- **`review/*`**: Service unit tests (queue, decisions, enrichment failure non-fatal); Flask test client for all routes (200/400/404/503, invalid action, display/serialisation errors).
- **`apply/engine.py`**: Dry-run (including no decisions); apply; backup; rollback; audit; apply/rollback raise when run_config or backup is missing/invalid; receipt not moved on amount mismatch.
- **`state/repository.py`**: Roundtrip and corrupt/malformed JSONL (decisions, skips, audit log) skip bad lines and continue.
- **`services/pipeline.py`**: Full-run integration; account_paths and run_config persisted; build_proposals/run raise when GnuCash is invalid.

